P. 940 (1917); Brennan v. Southern Express Co., 106 S.C. 102, 90
S.E. 402 (1916) (dictum). </p>

<p>157 245 U.S. 304 (1917). </p>

<p>158 Id. at 307-08 (citations omitted). </p>

<p>159 See text at note 126 supra. </p>

<p>160 245 U.S. at 308. </p>

<p>161 Eg., Slaughter House Cases, 83 U.S. (16 Wall.) 36 (1873). </p>

<p>162 Substantive due process was slowly being watered down even
in the economic area during this time. See, e.g., Muller v.
Oregon, 208 U.S. 412 (1908). </p>

<p>163 E.g., Bronaugh, Limiting or Prohibiting the Possession, of
Intoxicating Liquors for Personal Use, 23 LAW NoTEs 67 (1919);
