charging simply sale or possession of &quot;narcotic drugs&quot;
without specifying marijuana. On the same day, the court reversed
convictions in Baker v. State, 123 Tex. Crim. 209. 58 S.W.2d 534
(1933) (possession); Baker v. State, 123 Tex. Crim. 212, 58
