Cal Rptr. 725 (Dist, Ct. App. 1963) (agent alleged to be paid by
government if successful was only witness against defendant). </p>

<p>60 See People v. Carrasco, 159 Cal. App. 2d 63, 32i P.2d 129
(Dist. Ct. App. 1958), People v. Antista, 129 Cal. App. 2d 47,
276 P.2d 177 (Dist. Ct. App. 1954) (defendant never reported
having previously used marijuana and apartment used by many other
persons); People v. Candiotto, 128 Cal. App. 2d 347, 275 P.2d 500
(Dist. Ct. App. 1954); People v. Savage, 128 Cal. App. 2d 123,
274 P.2d 905 (Dist. Ct. App. 1954) (maid found marijuana wrapped
in napkins two days after a party held to be insufficient
evidence) (trial judge held to be prejudiced); Fawcett V. State,
