that has been scraped from the leaves and flowering tops of the
female plant; hashish or ganja-an agglomeration of female
flowering tops and stems with whatever resin is attached to their
surfaces, thought to contain about 40% resin; and marijuana-a low
potency preparation consisting of dried mature leaves and
flowering tops of both male and female plants, thought to contain
between 5 and 8% resin. Schwarz, Toward a Medical Understanding
of Marihuana, 14 CAN. PSYCHIATRIC ASS'N J. 591, 592 (1969). </p>

